		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				***Anon has nothing to do with rpin*** <br>  <br> In fact, it has everything to do with it. <br> In D&amp;D, a game that set the standard for what RP is: <br>  <br> You walk up to meet someone. Do you already know they are a rogue or necro? Or even a warrior? only class I can see identifying from a distance would be a cleric because of their holy symbol, but even those can be hidden so they dont get stolen.  <br>  <br> You can't just walk up to someone and know what they are, or their level. &quot;Level&quot; and &quot;Class&quot; are Out Of Character terms anyhow, and doesnt belong in a real role playing game. Nothing that is a game mechanic should be mentioned in character. <br>  <br> /con if you want to find their level. <br> Group with someone , or watch them to find out what class they are.  <br> Do things in a True RPG fashion, not the powergamer EQ tradition.
