			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Beta expreses a valid opinion which many others do agree with. However, just as many others disagree. <br>  <br> Anon makes sense on a roleplaying server. It makes sense because /who doesn't. I wouldn't be rid of either. /who is a vaguely helpful, if not specifically useful, function.  <br>  <br> I use /who to find friends, guilds I wish to keep in contact with, and, in my bored moments, other folk with Val at the begining of their name, just so I can frown. :P <br>  <br> When I see someone I think I want to meet, I walk up and start talking. This really isn't all that dificult. I've rarely been without a goup when I want one. I've run across continents, sailed between them, just to join up with one or two people I've contacted who mentioned they could use a hand. <br>  <br> It can difficult to break old habits, especially the easy, (read lazy perhaps?), habits. People will either make the effort, or leave. Verant should not change anything. I have spoken with more people who will leave if they do, than otherwise. <br>  <br> Oh, and the low population is due to the lack of twinks who cannot actually play the game without cheating, and the lack of frustrated d00ds who couldn't sound as stupid as they wanted due to the language barrier. <br>  <br> Good. <br>  <br> Vallaelanan <br> 		

